  "prompt": "Did I ate too much today?",
  "response": "I'm sorry you're feeling this way. Determining whether you've eaten too much can depend on several factors, including how you feel physically and emotionally. Here are a few signs that might indicate you've overeaten:\n\n1. **Physical Discomfort:** Feeling overly full, bloated, or experiencing stomach pain after eating.\n2. **Lethargy:** Feeling unusually tired or sluggish after a meal.\n3. **Guilt or Regret:** Experiencing negative emotions about the amount or type of food consumed.\n4. **Digestive Issues:** Having difficulty digesting food, such as experiencing heartburn or indigestion.\n5. **Frequent Overeating:** Regularly eating more than your body needs, which might lead to weight gain over time.\n\nIf you're concerned about your eating habits or how much you're eating, it might be helpful to:\n\n- **Keep a Food Diary:** Tracking what and when you eat can provide insights into your eating patterns.\n- **Listen to Your Body:** Pay attention to hunger and fullness cues to help regulate portion sizes.\n- **Seek Professional Advice:** A healthcare provider or a registered dietitian can offer personalized guidance and support.\n\nRemember, everyone's nutritional needs are different, and occasional overeating is normal. However, if it's a frequent issue or causing you distress, reaching out to a professional can be beneficial.",
